The Durban University of Technology (DUT) has dismissed claims that there are poor security controls on its campuses. Students at the university embarked on a march on Monday over safety concerns after one of their own was stabbed. Classes have been suspended until Thursday. Sandile Ndlovu, a student at the institution, is receiving treatment in hospital after being stabbed. The university says millions have been invested to ensure the safety of students and staff. <a href="https://iono.fm/e/746194">Content hosted by iono.fm</a>